entries.title: Venezuela's U.S.-Backed Opposition Removes Juan Guaidó as Leader
entries.description: The move marked an end to a political gambit in which he was recognized as the country’s legitimate president as part of an unsuccessful bid to oust authoritarian Nicolás Maduro from power.

entries.title: China Promotes U.S. Ambassador to Foreign Minister
entries.description: Qin Gang is seen as a trusted subordinate to Chinese President Xi Jinping and is a leading proponent of a combative approach to foreign policy.

entries.title: Aung San Suu Kyi to Serve 33 Years in Prison After Series of Trials
entries.description: A Myanmar court found the deposed leader guilty of corruption and handed down a seven-year sentence—the last in a series of verdicts against her that add up to 33 years in prison.

entries.title: In China, Travelers Avoid the Last Days of Quarantine
entries.description: Some groups of Chinese travelers have staged spot protests against being sent into still-mandatory quarantine—and they have won.

entries.title: Russia's Oil Ban Accelerates Shift in Global Energy Flows
entries.description: Russian crude is increasingly heading east to China and India, while Middle East producers are trying to sell more oil to premium-paying Europe.

entries.title: Russia Follows Ukraine Missile Barrage With Wave of Drones
entries.description: Russia launched more than a dozen armed drones at Ukrainian cities and infrastructure overnight, including one that struck and set fire to a district government building in Kyiv, Ukrainian authorities said.

entries.title: Cambodia Casino Fire Death Toll Rises to 25 as Search for Bodies Continues
entries.description: The fire, which burned for 17 hours before it was extinguished, may have been caused by an electrical problem, an initial investigation showed .

entries.title: American Spy Plane Has Uncomfortably Close Encounter with Chinese Jet Fighter
entries.description: The U.S. military said a Chinese jet fighter conducted an unsafe maneuver in international airspace over the South China Sea last week.
